race.comment: NEW YORK SCANDAL (9) found one better at The Parks in South Australia and then missed a nose at Yarra Valley as a $3.60 favourite. Maps much better today and keeps the handy 3kg claim. She deserves another win and finds a suitable race. AKA DAKA (7) is free running and brings a neck defeat from Tatura over a mile well-supported. He will skip across and back a touch in grade is a decent chance to go one better. ALGADON STORM (10) won her Maiden at Yarra Valley over 1514m with a bit in hand. Maps well and has scope for more improvement. She won't have to improve much to feature. FROZEN TIDE (3) was heading in the right direction before a plainer effort at Kyneton. Has a wide gate but is much better placed back to a 56 and should be right around the mark.
